hopobject.body: I'd like to change some money cost of prescription drugs in america Schechel laced his words with profanity and masked his emotion with sarcasm as he smoked cigarettes at his kitchen table during the hourlong interview. A bag filled with prescription medication sat on the table. Schechel, a retired bus driver with a clean driving record, said he left a friend's candy store in South Nyack and was returning home when the crash happened. He didn't even realize he was on the bridge, he said.
